DESCRIPTION:Create and connect every first\, second\, and third Saturday. T
	his lively space is filled with hands-on art making\, concerts\, and momen
	ts of community-all inspired by SAM's permanent collections and exhibition
	s. Whether you're an art enthusiast\, a curious newcomer\, or just looking
	 for a place to recharge this weekend\, you're always welcome. Learn about
	 the artwork through interactive activities\, meet new friends\, or simply
	 enjoy the atmosphere before exploring the galleries. Programs in SAM's en
	try gathering spaces are always free and open to everyone. Food and bevera
	ges from Shooby Doo Catering will be available for purchase in theBrotman 
	Forum. Bring your curiosity and imagination\, we'll provide the rest. 11 a
	m-2 pm | Jazz with Beserat Tafesse South Hall Trombonist Beserat Tafesse a
	nd his band of cutting-edge musicians define the present-day sound of Jazz
	 in Seattle.Born to Ethiopian immigrants in the Pacific Northwest\, Besera
	t Tafesse grew up with a wide array of musical and cultural influences. Af
	ter cementing his love for Jazz\, he attended the Manhattan School of Musi
	c\, studying Jazz Trombone with some of the greats\, and shedding nightly 
	with many of New York's living legends. Now making Seattle his home once a
	gain\, Beserat is at the center of the Jazz community's most inspired musi
	c.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/saturdays-at-sam/16949
	695/2026-04-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
